9 Appointment Booking Logic (IMPORTANT)

Appointment.jsx

jsx
import { useState } from "react";

export default function Appointment() {
  const [form, setForm] = useState({
    name: "",
    phone: "",
    date: "",
  });

  const submitHandler = (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    alert(`Appointment booked for ${form.name}`);
    setForm({ name: "", phone: "", date: "" });
  };

  return (
    <section id="appointment" className="py-20">
      <h2 className="text-center text-3xl font-bold text-primary">
        Book Appointment
      </h2>

      <form
        onSubmit={submitHandler}
        className="max-w-md mx-auto mt-8 bg-white shadow p-6 rounded-xl"
      >
        <input
          className="w-full mb-4 p-3 border rounded"
          placeholder="Name"
          value={form.name}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, name: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <input
          className="w-full mb-4 p-3 border rounded"
          placeholder="Phone"
          value={form.phone}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, phone: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <input
          type="date"
          className="w-full mb-4 p-3 border rounded"
          value={form.date}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, date: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <button className="w-full bg-primary text-white py-3 rounded">
          Confirm Booking
        </button>
      </form>
    </section>
  );
}

Here are the correct & clean Tailwind-related links for the HTML <head> depending on how youre using Tailwind.

CASE 1: Vite + React + Tailwind (RECOMMENDED )

You do NOT add a Tailwind CDN link in this setup.

Your index.html should look like this:

index.html

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/vite.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    <!-- SEO -->
    <title>PhysioCare | Professional Physiotherapy</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Professional physiotherapy services for pain relief, rehabilitation, and recovery."
    />

    <!-- Fonts -->
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@400;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>

Tailwind is injected via index.css
Faster, optimized build
Portfolio / production ready

CASE 2: Tailwind CDN (NOT for Vite/React)

Only use this if you are NOT using Vite + React.

<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>

  • Vite

  • Production apps

  • Portfolios

Final Improved Appointment.jsx

jsx
import { useState } from "react";
import { motion } from "framer-motion";

export default function Appointment() {
  const [form, setForm] = useState({
    name: "",
    phone: "",
    date: "",
  });
  const [success, setSuccess] = useState(false);

  const submitHandler = (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setSuccess(true);
    setForm({ name: "", phone: "", date: "" });

    setTimeout(() => setSuccess(false), 3000);
  };

  return (
    <section id="appointment" className="py-24 bg-white">
      {/* Heading */}
      <div className="text-center max-w-xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 className="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-800">
          Book an Appointment
        </h2>
        <p className="mt-3 text-gray-500">
          Schedule a consultation with our certified physiotherapists.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Form */}
      <motion.form
        initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
        whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
        transition={{ duration: 0.6 }}
        onSubmit={submitHandler}
        className="max-w-md mx-auto mt-12 bg-emerald-50 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-sm"
      >
        {success && (
          <div className="mb-4 text-center text-emerald-600 font-medium">
             Appointment booked successfully!
          </div>
        )}

        <input
          className="w-full mb-4 p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-emerald-500"
          placeholder="Full Name"
          value={form.name}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, name: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <input
          className="w-full mb-4 p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-emerald-500"
          placeholder="Phone Number"
          value={form.phone}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, phone: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <input
          type="date"
          className="w-full mb-6 p-3 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-emerald-500"
          value={form.date}
          onChange={(e) => setForm({ ...form, date: e.target.value })}
          required
        />

        <motion.button
          whileHover={{ scale: 1.03 }}
          whileTap={{ scale: 0.97 }}
          className="w-full bg-emerald-600 text-white py-3 rounded-full font-medium hover:bg-emerald-700 transition"
        >
          Confirm Booking
        </motion.button>
      </motion.form>
    </section>
  );
}

Why this is happening

What youre seeing

  • Navbar

The real reason

HTML works like this:

Your <section> elements use:

At least take full viewport height

1. Active Section Highlight (Scroll Spy)

Why

  • Big UX upgrade

What it looks like

  • Current section text turns emerald

  • Underline stays visible

jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";
import { motion } from "framer-motion";

const sections = [
  { label: "Home", id: "home" },
  { label: "Services", id: "services" },
  { label: "About", id: "about" },
  { label: "Reviews", id: "reviews" },
  { label: "Gallery", id: "gallery" },
  { label: "Contact", id: "appointment" },
];

export default function Navbar() {
  const [active, setActive] = useState("home");

  useEffect(() => {
    const handleScroll = () => {
      sections.forEach((section) => {
        const el = document.getElementById(section.id);
        if (!el) return;

        const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
        if (rect.top <= 120 && rect.bottom >= 120) {
          setActive(section.id);
        }
      });
    };

    window.addEventListener("scroll", handleScroll);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("scroll", handleScroll);
  }, []);

  return (
    <motion.nav className="fixed top-0 w-full bg-white/90 backdrop-blur shadow-sm z-50">
      <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">

        <h1 className="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-600">PhysioCare</h1>

        <ul className="hidden md:flex gap-8">
          {sections.map((s) => (
            <li key={s.id}>
              <a
                href={`#${s.id}`}
                className={`relative font-medium transition
                  ${
                    active === s.id
                      ? "text-emerald-600"
                      : "text-gray-600 hover:text-emerald-600"
                  }`}
              >
                {s.label}
                {active === s.id && (
                  <span className="absolute left-0 -bottom-1 w-full h-[2px] bg-emerald-600" />
                )}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        <a
          href="#appointment"
          className="bg-emerald-600 text-white px-5 py-2 rounded-full text-sm"
        >
          Book Appointment
        </a>
      </div>
    </motion.nav>
  );
}

FINAL NAVBAR WITH HAMBURGER + ANIMATION

Navbar.jsx

jsx
import { useState } from "react";
import { motion, AnimatePresence } from "framer-motion";

const links = [
  { label: "Home", href: "#home" },
  { label: "Services", href: "#services" },
  { label: "About", href: "#about" },
  { label: "Reviews", href: "#reviews" },
  { label: "Gallery", href: "#gallery" },
  { label: "Contact", href: "#appointment" },
];

export default function Navbar() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

  return (
    <motion.nav
      initial={{ y: -40, opacity: 0 }}
      animate={{ y: 0, opacity: 1 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.6 }}
      className="fixed top-0 w-full bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-md shadow-sm z-50"
    >
      <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex justify-between items-center">

        {/* Logo */}
        <h1 className="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-emerald-600">
          PhysioCare
        </h1>

        {/* Desktop Menu */}
        <ul className="hidden md:flex gap-8 text-gray-600 font-medium">
          {links.map((l) => (
            <li key={l.label}>
              <a
                href={l.href}
                className="hover:text-emerald-600 transition"
              >
                {l.label}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        {/* Desktop CTA */}
        <a
          href="#appointment"
          className="hidden md:inline bg-emerald-600 text-white px-5 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-medium hover:bg-emerald-700 transition"
        >
          Book Appointment
        </a>

        {/* Hamburger Button */}
        <button
          onClick={() => setOpen(!open)}
          className="md:hidden relative w-8 h-8 flex flex-col justify-center items-center"
        >
          <span
            className={`absolute h-[2px] w-6 bg-gray-800 transition-transform duration-300
              ${open ? "rotate-45" : "-translate-y-2"}`}
          />
          <span
            className={`absolute h-[2px] w-6 bg-gray-800 transition-opacity duration-300
              ${open ? "opacity-0" : "opacity-100"}`}
          />
          <span
            className={`absolute h-[2px] w-6 bg-gray-800 transition-transform duration-300
              ${open ? "-rotate-45" : "translate-y-2"}`}
          />
        </button>
      </div>

      {/* Mobile Menu */}
      <AnimatePresence>
        {open && (
          <motion.div
            initial={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
            animate={{ height: "auto", opacity: 1 }}
            exit={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
            transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
            className="md:hidden bg-white border-t"
          >
            <ul className="flex flex-col gap-6 px-6 py-6 text-gray-700 font-medium">
              {links.map((l) => (
                <li key={l.label}>
                  <a
                    href={l.href}
                    onClick={() => setOpen(false)}
                    className="block hover:text-emerald-600 transition"
                  >
                    {l.label}
                  </a>
                </li>
              ))}

              <a
                href="#appointment"
                onClick={() => setOpen(false)}
                className="mt-2 bg-emerald-600 text-white text-center py-3 rounded-full font-medium"
              >
                Book Appointment
              </a>
            </ul>
          </motion.div>
        )}
      </AnimatePresence>
    </motion.nav>
  );
}
